Author: Jiannan Wang <jiannanwang@meta.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 23 00:56:10 2026 -0700

    Precompute CUPTI sync processing state before trace materialization (#1373)

    Summary:
    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/kineto/pull/1373

    Precompute CUPTI processing state before materializing activities so CUDA sync and event records can resolve device and wait metadata even when the kernel or event that establishes that state arrives later in the trace.

    In pass 1, we scan the raw CUPTI records and build the four lookup maps needed by later processing:

    - cpuCorrelationMap_
    - userCorrelationMap_
    - ctxToDeviceId()
    - waitEventMap()

    Those maps provide the CPU/user external-correlation links, the contextId -> deviceId mapping, and the CUDA event record metadata needed by sync activities.

    In pass 2, we do the actual trace processing and activity materialization. At that point, all required lookup state is already available, so sync/event handling no longer depends on record arrival order. This fixes the out-of-order case where synchronization records can appear before the CUDA event record or before the activity that establishes the context/device mapping.

    Because pass 1 now precomputes the sync lookup state, Event Synchronize no longer needs deferred logging. Only Stream Wait Event is still deferred, since that deferral is still used for the existing filtering of noisy waits on streams with no GPU activity.

    One thing to notice, currently if a contextId is not present in ctxToDeviceId(), the code assigns device 0 by default. This sounds like a hardcoded bug to me, but I haven't heard any real bug related to this.
      uint32_t contextIdtoDeviceId(uint32_t contextId) {
        auto it = ctxToDeviceId().find(contextId);
        return it != ctxToDeviceId().end() ? it->second : 0;
      }

    Reviewed By: ryanzhang22

    Differential Revision: D101828868

