    Fix NCCL metadata missing on GPU kernels due to CUPTI buffer ordering (#1354)

    Summary:
    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/kineto/pull/1354

    CUPTI provides no ordering guarantee for activity records in its buffers. When EXTERNAL_CORRELATION records (which link GPU kernels to CPU ops like NCCL record_param_comms) arrive after their corresponding CONCURRENT_KERNEL records, the linkedActivity() lookup fails because cpuCorrelationMap_ has not been populated yet. This causes all NCCL collective metadata (collective name, dtype, message sizes, group size, etc.) to be silently dropped from
    GPU kernel trace output.

    Fix: Split processGpuActivities into two passes over the CUPTI activity buffer:
    - Pass 1: Process only EXTERNAL_CORRELATION records to fully populate cpuCorrelationMap_ and userCorrelationMap_.
    - Pass 2: Process all remaining activities (kernels, sync events, etc.) which can now resolve their linked CPU activity regardless of buffer order.

    Reviewed By: ryanzhang22

    Differential Revision: D100050069

