    Summary:
    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/kineto/pull/1347

    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/kineto/pull/1346

    Move cuptiActivityGetNumDroppedRecords() outside the mutex_ scope in
    bufferCompleted(). When VLOG_IS_ON(1), this call re-enters CUPTI and needs
    its internal rwlock, while bufferRequested() acquires mutex_ under that same
    rwlock - creating a deadlock in multi-threaded environments (free-threaded
    Python / no-GIL).

    This follows the same pattern already used in activityBuffers() and
    clearActivities(), which explicitly release mutex_ before CUPTI calls with
    the comment: "Can't hold mutex_ during this call".

