commit 520b0564cdcb1efefadfe6e69894fbcba1870395
Author: Raymond Li <raymo@meta.com>
Date:   Mon Mar 2 21:22:37 2026 -0800

    Stream track descriptors before events in PerfettoTraceBuilder

    Summary:
    Track descriptors were only written at the end of the trace file (in
    writeToFile), after all events had been streamed. This forced readers
    to do a two-pass parse: first scanning for descriptors, then processing
    events.

    Fix this with three changes:

    1. Reorder output_membuf::log() so handleDeviceInfo/handleResourceInfo
       run before handleActivity. This ensures descriptors have correct
       names (not placeholders) before any events are written.

    2. Stream each descriptor immediately when created (if the output stream
       is available). The constructor-buffered descriptors (root process,
       Spans) are flushed when initializeOutputStream is called.

    3. Re-stream updated descriptors in handleDeviceInfo/handleResourceInfo
       when names change, including propagating names to child tracks via
       subTrackMap.

    Reviewed By: mzzchy

    Differential Revision: D94727132

