Author: Scott Schneider <scottas@meta.com>
Date:   Fri Feb 20 16:59:38 2026 -0800

    pull misnamed .cpp file into .h (#1270)

    Summary:
    Pull Request resolved: https://github.com/pytorch/kineto/pull/1270

     Moves the entire contents of `CuptiActivity.cpp` into `CuptiActivity.h`.

    The file `CuptiActivity.cpp` was not really a normal C++ source file. It was actually the inlined implementations for the generics declared in `CuptiActivity.h`. This meant that `CuptiActivityProfiler.cpp` had the line:
    ```
    #include "CuptiActivity.cpp"
    ```
    That is, at the least, confusing. The normal expectation for C++ code is that a `.h` is a header file that will be `#include`ed and a `.cpp` is a source file that will be compiled. I think we should stick to that.

