commit cd8d31902233a7887b630a4eca605f9529168923
Author: Nadav Rotem <nrotem@meta.com>
Date:   Sat May 31 17:22:10 2025 -0700

    Record dynamic device kernel launches in libkineto

    Summary:
    The PyTorch profiler relies on libkineto to collect cupti events from Nvidia GPUs. Cupti events are performance counters that expose internal statistics, such as bytes written to DRAM and SM utilization. Libkineto collects two kinds of events: kernel launches and cupti events. It calls logKernelName every time a kernel is launched. The code in addRangeEvents assumes the number of kernel names matches the number of events.

    However, this mechanism does not handle kernel launches initiated by the device. This commit changes how we track kernel launches to use cupti activities instead of host events. With this change we register the kernel parameters when handling the CUPTI_ACTIVITY_KIND_CONCURRENT_KERNEL event.

    T225612808

    Reviewed By: briancoutinho

    Differential Revision: D75538012

    fbshipit-source-id: a5323542178841fd17f5b7fb7e457e69610ec345
