    Add more configs to test CUDA runtime corner cases

    Summary:
    The stress test is a code that we use to explore the limits of the CUDA runtime and CUDA devices This diff adds a few changes to the stress test:

    - New parameters that control the grid dimensions of the CUDA kernels that execute on the GPU, the delay between collecting a trace and whether to run a warm-up before collecting a GPU trace
